Available Tools: create_network | list_networks | create_volume | list_volumes | mount_volume
Call Schema: { "func_call": "string", "name": "string", "driver": "string", "container_id": "string", "mount_path": "string" }
Response Schema: { "id": "string", "name": "string", "driver": "string", "scope": "string", "containers": ["string"] }
---
Question: Create a persistent volume for a PostgreSQL database and mount it to the running database container.
Call: { "func_call": "mount_volume", "name": "pg_data_vol", "driver": "local", "container_id": "c8f9a2b1d3e4", "mount_path": "/var/lib/postgresql/data" }
Response: { "id": "vol_9x8y7z6w5v", "name": "pg_data_vol", "driver": "local", "scope": "local", "containers": ["c8f9a2b1d3e4"] }

